The people are good, bad, ugly, beautiful, selfish, depressed, found, or lost.
But from the moment the reader of this book feels the passion for music in Mick Kelly's soul, and her yearning to soar above the squalor and desperation of the small town, then the author reveals her own soul with her words, for those that pick up on what her words show.
I am still amazed at the power this book has.
